Because the lines between public health, politics, and business have been blurred as a result of this pandemic, I have a difficult time fully trusting the Covid-19 vaccine in terms of its safety and effectiveness. I do not care for the propaganda the media has been using to push the vaccine and it makes me question the true motives behind why the vaccine is being pushed in the way that it is. Although the "science" that is behind the vaccine today may be showing that it is safe and effective, it could potentially be "science" in the future that shows unforeseen long term effects or even ineffectiveness. I was vaccinated simply because I was required to be for work. With that say, I am absolutely opposed to any form of vaccine mandate and it is very likely that I would still be unvaccinated today had it not be required. I have not seen any evidence that the vaccine is effective in preventing someone from contracting Covid-19. Rather, I look at it as a means of protecting oneself from a severe and potentially fatal form of the virus. However, the survival rate for the virus is already over 99%. As a healthy adult with no underlying health issues, I do not see an overwhelming need for the vaccine. You can still spread Covid-19 even when vaccinated so I am not buying into the argument that you are getting the vaccine to protect others. There are so many hypocritical arguments and overwhelming inconsistencies regarding Covid-19 protocols and restrictions that at this point it is hard to trust anything related to the pandemic. Look at the stands jam packed with people standing and sitting on top of each other at sporting events on television. These people are unmasked because they are outdoors and screaming and yelling while cheering on their team. The "science" says that because they are outdoors there is minimal risk of spreading Covid.
